description.narrative: A child- and gender-sensitive social welfare system is well advanced towards delivery of increasingly accessible and quality services for vulnerable children and families,which contributes to Access To Justice, Child Protection Systems, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Improved prevention of and responding to violence, abuse, exploitation and unnecessary separation of children.
